rComments: I have no clue why UTM hired him to teach BIO304, I have taken over 10 higher level bio courses, worst prof ever, UTM should stick to prof. stewart or lange or their own physiology profs, made a very interesting course extremely dull

In short, Dr. Yagi is an ineffective instructor. He clearly does not make an effort to make his lectures engaging, and relies on heavily dated material. In light of what is going on in the insect physiology field, It is ridiculous that this course included nothing about genomics!

I'm here to vouch for Mr. Yagi. His speech is NOT incoherent and he is always willing to help whenever a student needs it.  I agree that his lectures are a little bland (b/c he reads straight off of his notes), but he his not a terrible prof.  What he lectures is reflected in what he discusses and he is fair with his marking.

Very incoherent. Very George Bush-like in the way he lecturers. I can see why he never got promoted and is still a "Lecturer" at this point in his career. If you have no idea, just attend on of his classes and listen to the way he explains or teaches. You will end up 10x leaving the classroom. Yagi, leave the lecturing to people who can SPEAK.

This guy can't speak for the life of him. Stutters, mumbles. It's hard to believe a person can obtain a Ph.D and still have such hard time putting simple english sentences together. He doesn't seem that bright or interested in the material either. He needs to learn how to speak and put simple sentences together. Learn ENGLISH !!!
